##################################################
#   Steps needed to run Monte Carlo simulation   #
##################################################
Step 1. read in data
    Functions needed:
        1) read in full symmetry equivalent clusters and convert then to vectors for C++
        2) read in str_list and convert to energy above hull or raw energy
Step 2. create MC session
    Functions needed:
        1) read in cluster expansion rules (motif and decoration) generated probably from python code
        2) create simulation cell with 
           a) neighbor list
           b) species list
           c) spin list
        2) read in session parameters, e.g. algorithm and spin model to use
Step 3. MC run
    Functions needed:
        1) atom swap, spin flip
        2) random number generator
        3) energy difference calculator
        4) output writer
